CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 8, 1961, pg. 1, reads: "Matriarch Breaks Ground - Mrs. Mamie Wilkins, center, only living charter member of Mt. Olive Baptist Church, Rankin, was key participant in ground-breaking ceremonies last Sunday. Mrs. Josephine French, left, a 50-year member, assists, while Mrs. Elvira Marks, daughter of Mrs. Wilkins, looks on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groundbreaking ceremony for Mt. Olive Baptist Church, with Mamie Wilkins, and man holding robe, possibly Rev. Brannon Hopson, standing on sidewalk, Rankin
